      "date": "2013-02-02 16:59:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nGood catch.\n\nHowever, I find one part if the patch confusing and likely prone to errors. Using \"conservative\" for one function and \"is_reconnect\" in the other has exactly the opposite meaning. It would be better to use \"new_connection\" instead of \"is_reconnect\" so that the meaning of the argument stays the same between the functions.",
